	"keywords": "Web Development, Front End Development, Technology, Software Development, Design",
	"description": "Web accessibility is getting a lot of attention these days, but it can be\nintimidating. Here’s a simple introduction to web accessibility: what it is, why\nit’s important, and the benefits that come along with accessibility.\n\nAt the most basic level, web accessibility means building websites that are\nusable by as many people as possible.\n\nIn the US alone, 57 million people report having a disability. That’s one in\nevery five people — equivalent to the entire populations of New York and\nCalifornia",
